OL,3,CLife satisfaction in Jersey plummets,
OL,4,Cglobal study reveals
OL,6,FAround one in seven (14%) employees in
OL,7,FJersey worked 50 or more hours in a
OL,8,Ftypical week during 2022, which is
OL,9,Fhigher than in the UK (11%) and the
OL,10,FOECD average (12%).
OL,12,FAcross other metrics, the homicide
OL,13,Frate in Jersey between 2018 and 2020
OL,14,Fwas 0.6 per 100,000 people,
OL,15,Fsignificantly lower than the OECD
OL,16,Faverage of 5.9.
